article.headline: Iowa State 76, Liberty 58
article.story: AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Freshman Curtis Stinson had 17 points, 10 rebounds and five assists and Iowa State remained unbeaten with a 76-58 victory over Liberty on Saturday. Jared Homan added 15 points and four blocks, while Jake Sullivan scored 14 for the Cyclones, who made Wayne Morgan the school's first coach to start 5-0 in his first season. Iowa State used a 16-0 run to pull away after leading by only six with a little more than 11 minutes left. Larry Blair led Liberty (3-6) with 23 points. He and Gabe Martin, who finished with 11, accounted for all of Liberty's points in the first half, which ended with Iowa State ahead 32-22. Iowa State never trailed after Jackson Vroman's putback off his own missed free throw pulled the Cyclones into a 5-all tie. A 16-5 run stretched Iowa State's lead to 23-12 with less than seven minutes remaining in the half. Martin's 3-pointer and two baskets by Blair got the Flames to within 10 at halftime, and they cut the lead to 34-29 early in the second half. Homan then scored eight straight Iowa State points to help the Cyclones build a 42-31 lead before Liberty made one more run, using a 9-2 spurt to draw to 44-38 with 11:49 to play. But Iowa State scored the next 16 points to break it open. Stinson, Homan and Sullivan each scored four points during the run, which ended with Stinson getting a basket on a goal-tending call. Iowa State led by as many as 27 points in the final minutes.
